Movie Search Application
This is a simple web application that allows users to search for movies using the OMDB API. Users can enter a movie title in the search box, and the application fetches movie information from the OMDB API and displays it to the user.

Features
Live Movie Search: Instantly search for movies as you type in the search box.
Detailed Movie Information: Click on a movie in the search results to view detailed information about the selected movie.
Responsive Design: The application is designed to work seamlessly on desktop and mobile devices.
Technologies Used
HTML: For the basic structure of the web page.
CSS: For styling the user interface and ensuring a visually appealing layout.
JavaScript: For handling user interactions, making API requests, and dynamically updating the content.
Usage

.

API Key
This application uses the OMDB API to fetch movie data. You will need to obtain an API key from OMDB API and replace 'YOUR_API_KEY' in the JavaScript code with your actual API key for the application to work correctly.

How to Contribute
If you want to contribute to this project, follow these steps:

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch for your feature: git checkout -b feature-name
Commit your changes: git commit -m 'Add new feature'
Push to the branch: git push origin feature-name
Submit a pull request.
